# Supabase credentials - replace with values from your Supabase dashboard
# See instructions below.

NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# =============================================================================
# HOW TO GET YOUR SUPABASE CREDENTIALS
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com and create a free account (or log in)
#
# 2. Create a new project:
#    - Click "New Project"
#    - Set a project name (e.g., "AI Radar")
#    - Set a strong database password (save it somewhere safe)
#    - Choose a region closest to your users
#
# 3. Get your API URL:
#    - Go to Project Settings (gear icon) > API
#    - Copy the "Project URL" (looks like: https://xxxxx.supabase.co)
#    - Set it as NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL above
#
# 4. Get your service role key:
#    - Go to Project Settings > API
#    - Under "Project API keys", find "service_role" (secret key)
#    - Click "Reveal" and copy the key
#    - Set it as SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY above
#    - NOTE: Never expose the service_role key in client-side code!
#
# 5. Update frontend/.env.local with the same NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
#    and set NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY to the "anon" key from
#    the same API settings page (NOT the service_role key).
#
# =============================================================================
# HOW TO APPLY MIGRATIONS AND SEED DATA
# =============================================================================
#
# Option A: Using the Supabase Dashboard (easiest)
#   1. Go to your project at https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/xxxxx
#   2. Open the SQL Editor
#   3. Copy the contents of supabase/migrations/001_initial_schema.sql
#   4. Paste and run it
#   5. For seeding, use the SQL Editor to insert data or use Option B
#
# Option B: Using the Supabase CLI (requires Docker)
#   1. Install Supabase CLI: https://supabase.com/docs/guides/local-development/cli/getting-started
#   2. Run: supabase link --project-ref <your-project-id>
#   3. Run: supabase db push
#   4. Then run the seed script:
#      npm install -D tsx   (if not already installed in frontend/)
#      npx tsx supabase/seed.ts
#
# Option C: Manual SQL insert (from SQL Editor)
#   Use INSERT INTO products (...) VALUES (...) statements.
#   The seed script (supabase/seed.ts) contains 22 pre-built products
#   that can be converted to SQL if needed.
#
# =============================================================================
